{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nTurn on the cross-ticket overlap detector (epic only-crave-art) for THIS project by\nsetting `verify.overlap_enabled = true` in the tracked project config `rebar.toml`.\nThe feature shipped gated OFF by default; this flips it on so plan-review runs the\nadvisory store-wide overlap step and surfaces `overlap[]` suggestions.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `rebar.toml` `[verify]` section sets `overlap_enabled = true` with an explanatory comment.\n- [ ] No other config keys change; the file still parses. Verified by\n      `python -c \"import tomllib; tomllib.load(open('rebar.toml','rb'))\"` exiting 0.\n- [ ] The local build reads the flag as true and the overlap step executes end-to-end:\n      `load_config('.').verify.overlap_enabled is True`, and `rebar review-plan <a ticket>`\n      returns a verdict carrying an `overlap` key (empty list is expected until digests are\n      enriched — the point is the step RAN, proving the flag is wired, not stale-global).\n- [ ] Commit references this ticket (rebar-ticket trailer) and passes `make lint`.\n- [ ] Change lands on `main` through Gerrit (LLM-Review +1 and Verified +1).\n\n## Scope\n\n- `rebar.toml` only. No source/behavior change — the flag is read by\n  `verify.overlap_enabled` (`src/rebar/_config_schema.py`). `rebar.toml` is the tracked,\n  git-committed project config (preferred by config discovery over the git-ignored\n  `.rebar/config.conf`), so the flag is persistent and shared for all contributors without\n  per-machine env-var setup. Rollback is setting it back to false.\n\n## Two consumers of the flag (behavioral note)\n\n`overlap_enabled` gates TWO independent code paths, not one — flipping it on activates both:\n\n1. **Plan-review overlap step** (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/`): the advisory two-stage\n   retrieve-then-rerank pass that populates `overlap[]` on the verdict. Advisory only —\n   never blocks a claim or close.\n2. **Opportunistic enrichment drain** (`src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py`, gated at the same\n   `verify.overlap_enabled` check, invoked from the ticket write paths in\n   `_store/event_append.py` and `_store/push.py`): asynchronously builds the BM25F digests\n   that stage-1 retrieval needs. This means every `rebar` ticket write may now opportunistically\n   trigger LLM enrichment (subject to the `[tool.rebar.llm] overlap_drain*` tunables and the\n   drain lease/soak rules). This is intentional — overlap detection needs enriched digests —\n   but it is a real latency/cost side-effect on write paths. Rollback (flag → false) disables\n   both paths together."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783684691016715001,"uuid":"106760b3-4702-46cc-9a43-086a901b718e"}